    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;A JSON Web Key (JWK) is a JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) data structure that represents a cryptographic key.  This specification also defines a JWK Set JSON data structure that represents a set of JWKs.  Cryptographic algorithms and identifiers for use with this specification are described in the separate JSON Web Algorithms (JWA) specification and IANA registries established by that specification.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
